						               													<description>In &amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#229;&amp;#175;&amp;#134; (Kuromitsu), the players are creating a hybrid word-search/crossword puzzle grid, and trying to score the most points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is given a different colored pencil, and a set of categories is laid out in a circle.  After some initial seeding, a player rolls a die, which determines the category of word to be added.  Then, in real-time, the first player to shout out a word in the category determines the word that will be written by each player on their board.  Afterwards, the papers are passed to the left, and the process is repeated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once a player is unable to write a word on their sheet the game ends.  Each player scores points based upon how many times their colored pencil has written letters on each sheet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
